snippet.title: The Conjuring: Last Rites | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Discover why this case ended it all. #TheConjuring: Last Rites - Only in Theaters September 5.

From New Line Cinema comes the ninth entry in the more than $2 billion theatrical Conjuring universe, The Conjuring: Last Rites, directed by franchise veteran Michael Chaves and produced by franchise architects James Wan and Peter Safran.

The Conjuring: Last Rites delivers another thrilling chapter of the iconic Conjuring cinematic universe, based on real events.  Vera Farmiga and Patrick Wilson reunite for one last case as renowned, real-life paranormal investigators Ed and Lorraine Warren in a powerful and spine-chilling addition to the global box office-breaking franchise.

Farmiga and Wilson star alongside Mia Tomlinson and Ben Hardy, who portray Ed and Lorraine’s daughter Judy Warren and her boyfriend, Tony Spera, as well as Steve Coulter returning as Father Gordon, Rebecca Calder, Elliot Cowan, Kíla Lord Cassidy, Beau Gadsdon, John Brotherton and Shannon Kook.

Chaves directs from a screenplay by Ian Goldberg & Richard Naing and David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick, story by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick & James Wan, based on characters created by Chad Hayes & Carey W. Hayes.  The executive producers are Michael Clear, Judson Scott, Hans Ritter, David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick, Natalia Safran, John Rickard and Michael Chaves.

Chaves is joined behind the camera by his creative team, including director of photography Eli Born, production designer John Frankish, editors Elliot Greenberg and Gregory Plotkin, visual effects supervisor Scott Edelstein, visual effects producer Eric Bruneau and costume designer Graham Churchyard, with casting by Rose Wicksteed and Sophie Kingston-Smith.  The music supervisor is Ian Broucek and the music is by composer Benjamin Wallfisch.

New Line Cinema Presents The Safran Company / An Atomic Monster Production, The Conjuring: Last Rites.  The film will be released worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures and will be only in theaters and IMAX® in North America on September 5, 2025, and internationally beginning 3 September 2025.

snippet.title: One Punch Man Season 3 - Official Trailer (English Subtitles)
snippet.description:
"One-Punch Man” returns with Season 3! Check out the latest trailer for the continuation of this series!

Saitama is a hero who only became a hero for fun. After three years of “special training,” he’s become so strong that he’s practically invincible. In fact, he’s too strong—even his mightiest opponents are taken out with a single punch. Alongside Genos, his faithful disciple, Saitama performs his official hero duties as a member of the Hero Association. One day, monsters claiming to be from the Monster Association suddenly appeared, taking a child of Hero Association executive hostage. The S-class heroes gather and plan a raid on the Monster Association hideout to rescue the hostage. Meanwhile, Garou, a “human monster” who was taken by the Monster Association during a battle with the heroes, awakens in the Monster Association hideout."

snippet.title: Avatar: Fire and Ash | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
From Director James Cameron, watch the trailer for Avatar: Fire and Ash.
Experience the film only in theaters December 19.

With “Avatar: Fire and Ash,” James Cameron takes audiences back to Pandora in an immersive new adventure with Marine turned Na’vi leader Jake Sully (Sam Worthington), Na’vi warrior Neytiri (Zoe Saldaña), and the Sully family. The film, which has a screenplay by James Cameron & Rick Jaffa & Amanda Silver, and a story by James Cameron & Rick Jaffa & Amanda Silver & Josh Friedman & Shane Salerno, also stars Sigourney Weaver, Stephen Lang, Oona Chaplin, Cliff Curtis, Britain Dalton, Trinity Bliss, Jack Champion, Bailey Bass and Kate Winslet.

What is Roblox? ROBLOX is an online virtual playground and workshop, where kids of all ages can safely interact, create, have fun, and learn. It’s unique in that practically everything on ROBLOX is designed and constructed by members of the community. ROBLOX is designed for 13 to 18 year olds, but it is open to people of all ages. Each player starts by choosing an avatar and giving it an identity. They can then explore ROBLOX — interacting with others by chatting, playing games, or collaborating on creative projects. Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything — be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer “Capture the Flag” game or some other, yet-to-be-dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (“Robux”). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.

snippet.title: Tom Jones, Engelbert, Andy Williams, Carpenters, Elvis Presley 🍀 Relaxing Oldies Songs 50s 60s 70s
snippet.description:
Relaxing Oldies Songs 50s 60s 70s – Enjoy a soothing collection of the most beautiful romantic classics from the golden era, featuring legendary artists such as Tom Jones, Engelbert Humperdinck, Andy Williams, The Carpenters, and Elvis Presley. Let the calming melodies and heartfelt lyrics take you back to a simpler time filled with love and unforgettable memories.

This timeless playlist of old love songs, golden oldies, and relaxing retro ballads is perfect for cozy evenings, peaceful mornings, or background music for working, reading, or reminiscing.

🎶 Featured Songs:

Tom Jones – Delilah, Green Green Grass of Home, It’s Not Unusual, Love Me Tonight, She’s a Lady
Engelbert Humperdinck – The Last Waltz, A Man Without Love, Release Me, There Goes My Everything, Spanish Eyes
Andy Williams – Moon River, Love Story (Where Do I Begin), Can’t Get Used to Losing You, Music to Watch Girls By, Speak Softly Love
The Carpenters – Close to You, Yesterday Once More, Superstar, We've Only Just Begun, For All We Know
Elvis Presley – Can’t Help Falling in Love, Love Me Tender, Always on My Mind, It’s Now or Never, Are You Lonesome Tonight

These relaxing classics are perfect for fans of vintage love songs, soft romantic ballads, and easy listening oldies. Let these nostalgic voices and melodies fill your heart with peace and romance.

snippet.title: Arthur Nery - Ayaw Baya (Official Visualizer)
snippet.description:
#ArthurNery #AyawBaya #vivarecords 

Stream now on all digital music platforms,

Composed by Arthur Madrigalejos Nery
Published by Viva Music Publishing, Inc.
Produced by Axel Fernandez, Arthur Nery, Ian Fajarito
Arranged by Arthur Nery, Axel Fernandez
A&R: Karl Art
Recorded by: Axel Fernandez
Mixed by Axel Fernandez
Mastered by Axel Fernandez
Drums: Bea Lao 
Bass guitar: Mike Bayas 
Electric guitar: Ivan Villaruel 
Piano: Ian Fajarito 
Saxophone: RM Piquero
Strings: Axel Fernandez
Cover Art Phot: Kris Cazin
 
Arthur Nery marks a heartfelt milestone in his career as he surprises fans with “Ayaw Baya” as his first-ever Bisaya single that pays homage to his Cagayan de Oro roots. Blending his signature soulful sound and regional lyricism, Arthur delivers a deeply personal track about love, abandonment, and openness. “Ayaw Baya” is both a tribute to his heritage and a powerful reminder of the pain that lingers when goodbyes are left unsaid.

Creative Direction by Arthur Nery 
Video Edited by Glendale 
Assisted and Photo by Arnold Pilapil
Video Producer: Ken Opina

Executive Producer: Vic del Rosario, Verb del Rosario
AVP for Artist Management and Label Relations: 
Sammy Samaniego
Artist Manager and Talent Development Manager: 
Chochay Magno
Marketing Department 
Label Manager: Emerson Abaraccoso 
Assistant Marketing Manager: Ken Opina 
YouTube Specialist: Paolo Bautista 

Arthur Nery GLAM Team 
Hair and Make Up Artist: Sharmaine de Castro 
Styled by Bettina Bañez

Di na gani ta magkasinabot
Di pa gyud dali puyukon
Pangga nga akong gipaabot
Sa lain man diay siya gaulian 

Kung sa ato pa
Wa diay damha
Ang atoang gihaguan
Oh nasinati ba
Nga satong duha 
Wala may kulang muhigugma

Oh ayaw
Ayaw baya 
Ay nala'g pasalig nga mubalik ka
Wa naman ka gani manamilit pa
Ayaw 
Ayna'g biya kung mubalik 
Ako ra amping kanimo

Unsa ra ni
Ang akoang bahandi
Kung di pud nako ni masubayan
Ikaw ra man 
Wa nakoy uban pa
Pahulama kos kasing-kasing

Imo ramang gugma ug hulagway 
Ang gabalik balik
O ikaw akong puhon ug kanunay

Kung sa ato pa
Wa diay damha
Ang atoang gihaguan
Oh nasinati ba
Nga satong duha
Wala may kulang muhigugma

Oh ayaw
Ayaw baya 
Ay nala'g pasalig nga mubalik ka
Wa naman ka gani manamilit pa
Ayaw 
Ayna'g biya kung mubalik 
Ako ra amping

Ayaw
Oh ayaw baya 
Ay nala'g pasalig nga mubalik ka
Wa naman ka gani manamilit pa
Ayaw 
Aynag biya kung mubalik 
Ako na amping

(ENGLISH TRANSLATION)

AYAW BAYA 
(Please) Don't

Verse 1
We haven't been seeing eye to eye
It's been hard to woo you
The love I wait for
Goes home to another

Refrain
I guess you could say
I guess you didn't expect
What we built
We can't feel
Though the love we shared
Was pure and fair

Chorus
Oh, don't 
Please don't 
Tell you’ll come home
When you gave no farewell
Don't 
Leave and return
I’ll love who you were

Verse 2
Of what worth is this wealth
If I can't follow through
It's only been you
Nothing and nobody but
So lend me your heart
‘Cos it's your love and your face
I revisit and return to
You are my soon and ever

I guess you didn't expect

Was pure and fair
